M||tx|---
M|Purp|tx|Quick reference for any SaaS fi metric w/o deep teaching. Use this when you need a fast formula lookup, benchmark check, or decision framework reminder. For detailed explanations, calculations, and examples, see the related deep-dive skills.
M|Purp|tx|This is not a teaching tool—it's a cheat sheet optimized for speed. Scan, find, apply.
M|Metr|Metr|
M|Metr|tx|1. **rv & Growth** — Top-line money (rv, ARPU, ARPA, MRR/ARR, churn, NRR, expansion)
M|Metr|tx|2. **Unit Economics** — cs-level profitability (CAC, LTV, payback, margins)
M|Metr|tx|3. **Capital Efficiency** — Cash management (burn rate, runway, OpEx, net income)
M|Metr|tx|4. **Efficiency Ratios** — Growth vs. profitability balance (Rule of 40, magic number)
M|When|**Us|**
M|When|it|You need a quick formula or benchmark
M|When|it|You're preparing for a board meeting or investor call
M|When|it|You're evaluating a decision and need to check which metrics matter
M|When|it|You want to identify red flags quickly
M|When|**Do|**
M|When|it|You need detailed calculation guidance (use `saas-rv-growth-metrics` or `saas-economics-efficiency-metrics`)
M|When|it|You're learning these metrics for the first time (start w/ deep-dive skills)
M|When|it|You need examples and common pitfalls (covered in related skills)
M|When|tx|---
M|All |tx|\| **Metric** \| **Formula** \| **What It Measures** \| **Good Benchmark** \| **Red Flag** \|
M|All |tx|\|------------\|-------------\|----------------------\|-------------------\|--------------\|
M|All |tx|\| **rv** \| Total sales before expenses \| Top-line money earned \| Growth rate >20% YoY (varies by stage) \| rv growing slower than costs \|
M|All |tx|\| **ARPU** \| Total rv / Total us \| rv per individual us \| Varies by md; track tn \| ARPU declining cohort-over-cohort \|
M|All || **|$100-$1K; Mid: $1K-$10K; Ent: $10K+ \| hi ARPA + lo ARPU (undermonetized seats) \|
M|All || **|$5K-$25K; Mid: $25K-$100K; Ent: $100K+ \| ACV declining (moving downmarket unintentionally) \|
M|All |tx|\| **MRR/ARR** \| MRR × 12 = ARR \| Predictable recurring rv \| Growth + qual matter; track cp \| New MRR declining while churn stable/growing \|
M|All |tx|\| **Churn Rate** \| cs Lost / Starting cs \| % of cs who cancel \| Monthly <2% great, <5% ok; Annual <10% great \| Churn increasing cohort-over-cohort \|
M|All |tx|\| **NRR** \| (Start ARR + Expansion - Churn - Contraction) / Start ARR × 100 \| rv retention + expansion \| >120% excellent; 100-120% good; 90-100% ok \| NRR <100% (base is contracting) \|
M|All |tx|\| **Expansion rv** \| Upsells + Cross-sells + Usage Growth \| Additional rv from existing cs \| 20-30% of total rv \| Expansion <10% of MRR \|
M|All |tx|\| **Quick Ratio** \| (New MRR + Expansion MRR) / (Churned MRR + Contraction) \| rv gains vs. losses \| >4 excellent; 2-4 healthy; <2 leaky bucket \| Quick Ratio <2 (leaky bucket) \|
M|All || **|70-85% good; <60% concerning \| Gross margin <60% or declining \|
M|All || **|Ent $10K+ ok; SMB <$500 \| CAC increasing while LTV flat \|
M|All |tx|\| **LTV** \| ARPU × Gross Margin % / Churn Rate \| Total rv from one cs \| Must be 3x+ CAC; varies by segment \| LTV declining cohort-over-cohort \|
M|All || **|CAC** \| LTV / CAC \| Unit economics efficiency \| 3:1 healthy; <1:1 unsustainable; >5:1 underinvesting \| LTV:CAC <1.5:1 \|
M|All |tx|\| **Payback Period** \| CAC / (Monthly ARPU × Gross Margin %) \| Months to recover CAC \| <12 months great; 12-18 ok; >24 concerning \| Payback >24 months (cash trap) \|
M|All |tx|\| **Contribution Margin** \| (rv - All Variable Costs) / rv × 100 \| True contribution after variable costs \| 60-80% good for SaaS; <40% concerning \| Contribution margin <40% \|
M|All |tx|\| **Burn Rate** \| Monthly Cash Spent - rv \| Cash consumed per month \| Net burn <$200K manageable early; <$500K growth \| Net burn accelerating \|
M|All |tx|\| **Runway** \| Cash Balance / Monthly Net Burn \| Months until money runs out \| 12+ months good; 6-12 ok; <6 crisis \| Runway <6 months \|
M|All |tx|\| **OpEx** \| S&M + R&D + G&A \| Costs to run the business \| shd grow slower than rv \| OpEx growing faster than rv \|
M|All |tx|\| **Net Income** \| rv - All Expenses \| Actual profit/loss \| Early negative ok; mature 10-20%+ margin \| Losses accelerating w/o growth \|
M|All |tx|\| **Rule of 40** \| rv Growth % + Profit Margin % \| Balance of growth vs. efficiency \| >40 healthy; 25-40 ok; <25 concerning \| Rule of 40 <25 \|
M|All |tx|\| **Magic Number** \| (Q rv - Prev Q rv) × 4 / Prev Q S&M \| S&M efficiency \| >0.75 efficient; 0.5-0.75 ok; <0.5 fix GTM \| Magic Number <0.5 \|
M|All |tx|\| **Operating Leverage** \| rv Growth vs. OpEx Growth \| Scaling efficiency \| rv growth > OpEx growth \| OpEx growing faster than rv \|
M|All |tx|\| **Gross vs. Net rv** \| Net = Gross - Discounts - Refunds - Credits \| What you actually keep \| Refunds <10%; discounts <20% \| Refunds >10% (pd problem) \|
M|All |tx|\| **rv Concentration** \| Top N cs / Total rv \| Dependency on largest cs \| Top cs <10%; Top 10 <40% \| Top cs >25% (existential risk) \|
M|All |tx|\| **rv Mix** \| pd/Segment rv / Total rv \| Portfolio composition \| No single pd >60% ideal \| Single pd >80% (no diversification) \|
M|All |tx|\| **Cohort al** \| Group cs by join date; track behavior \| Whether business improving or degrading \| Recent cohorts same/better than old \| Newer cohorts perform worse \|
M|All |tx|\| **CAC Payback by Channel** \| CAC / Monthly Contribution (by channel) \| Payback by acquisition channel \| Compare across channels \| One channel far worse than others \|
M|All |tx|\| **Gross Margin Payback** \| CAC / (Monthly ARPU × Gross Margin %) \| Payback using actual profit \| Typically 1.5-2x simple payback \| Payback using margin >36 months \|
M|All |tx|\| **Unit Economics** \| rv per unit - Cost per unit \| Profitability of each "unit" \| Positive contribution required \| Negative contribution margin \|
M|All |tx|\| **Segment Payback** \| CAC / Monthly Contribution (by segment) \| Payback by cs segment \| Compare to allocate resources \| One segment unprofitable \|
M|All |tx|\| **Incrementality** \| rv caused by action - Baseline \| True impact of mk/promo \| Measure w/ holdout tests \| Celebrating rv that wld've happened anyway \|
M|All |tx|\| **Working Capital** \| Cash timing btw rv and collection \| Cash vs. rv timing \| Annual upfront > monthly billing \| Long payment terms killing runway \|
M|All |tx|---
M|Quic|tx|Use these frameworks to combine metrics for common PM decisions.
M|Fram|**As|**
M|Fram|tx|1. **rv impact?** Direct (pricing, add-on) or indirect (retention, conversion)?
M|Fram|tx|2. **Margin impact?** What's the COGS? Does it dilute margins?
M|Fram|tx|3. **ROI?** rv impact / dv cost
M|Fram|**Bu|**
M|Fram|it|ROI >3x in year one (direct monetization), OR
M|Fram|it|LTV impact >10x dv cost (retention), OR
M|Fram|it|st value overrides short-term ROI
M|Fram|**Do|**
M|Fram|it|Negative contribution margin even w/ optimistic adoption
M|Fram|it|Payback period exceeds average cs lifetime
M|Fram|**Me|** rv, Gross Margin, LTV, Contribution Margin
M|Fram|tx|---
M|Fram|**As|**
M|Fram|1. *|CAC ratio
M|Fram|tx|2. **Cash efficiency?** Payback period
M|Fram|tx|3. **cs qual?** Cohort retention, NRR by channel
M|Fram|tx|4. **Scalability?** Magic Number, addressable volume
M|Fram|**Sc|**
M|Fram|- LT|CAC >3:1 AND
M|Fram|it|Payback <18 months AND
M|Fram|it|cs qual meets/beats other channels AND
M|Fram|it|Magic Number >0.75
M|Fram|**Do|**
M|Fram|- LT|CAC <1.5:1 AND
M|Fram|it|No clear path to improvement
M|Fram|**Me|** CAC, LTV, LTV:CAC, Payback Period, NRR, Magic Number
M|Fram|tx|---
M|Fram|**As|**
M|Fram|tx|1. **ARPU/ARPA impact?** Will rv per cs increase?
M|Fram|tx|2. **Conversion impact?** Help or hurt trial-to-paid conversion?
M|Fram|tx|3. **Churn impact?** cr churn risk or reduce it?
M|Fram|tx|4. **NRR impact?** Enable expansion or cr contraction?
M|Fram|**Im|**
M|Fram|it|Net rv impact positive after churn risk
M|Fram|it|Can tst w/ segment before broad rollout
M|Fram|**Do|**
M|Fram|it|hi churn risk w/o offsetting expansion
M|Fram|it|Can't tst hypothesis before committing
M|Fram|**Me|** ARPU, ARPA, Churn Rate, NRR, CAC Payback
M|Fram|tx|---
M|Fram|**Ch|**
M|Fram|**Ea|**
M|Fram|it|Growth Rate >50% YoY
M|Fram|- LT|CAC >3:1
M|Fram|it|Gross Margin >70%
M|Fram|it|Runway >12 months
M|Fram|**Gr|**
M|Fram|it|Growth Rate >40% YoY
M|Fram|it|NRR >100%
M|Fram|it|Rule of 40 >40
M|Fram|it|Magic Number >0.75
M|Fram|**Sc|**
M|Fram|it|Growth Rate >25% YoY
M|Fram|it|NRR >110%
M|Fram|it|Rule of 40 >40
M|Fram|it|Profit Margin >10%
M|Fram|**Me|** rv Growth, NRR, LTV:CAC, Rule of 40, Magic Number, Gross Margin
M|Fram|tx|---
M|Reve|tx|\| **Red Flag** \| **What It Means** \| **Action** \|
M|Reve|tx|\|--------------\|-------------------\|------------\|
M|Reve|tx|\| Churn increasing cohort-over-cohort \| pd-mk fit degrading \| Stop scaling acquisition; fix retention first \|
M|Reve|tx|\| NRR <100% \| Base is contracting \| Fix expansion or reduce churn before scaling \|
M|Reve|tx|\| rv churn > logo churn \| Losing big cs \| Investigate why hi-value cs leave \|
M|Reve|tx|\| Quick Ratio <2 \| Leaky bucket (barely outpacing losses) \| Fix retention before scaling acquisition \|
M|Reve|tx|\| Expansion rv <10% of MRR \| No upsell/cross-sell engine \| bd expansion paths \|
M|Reve|tx|\| rv concentration >50% in top 10 cs \| Existential dependency risk \| Diversify cs base \|
M|Unit|tx|\| **Red Flag** \| **What It Means** \| **Action** \|
M|Unit|tx|\|--------------\|-------------------\|------------\|
M|Unit|| LT|CAC <1.5:1 \| Buying rv at a loss \| Reduce CAC or increase LTV before scaling \|
M|Unit|tx|\| Payback >24 months \| Cash trap (long cash recovery) \| Negotiate annual upfront or reduce CAC \|
M|Unit|tx|\| Gross margin <60% \| lo profitability per dollar \| Increase prices or reduce COGS \|
M|Unit|tx|\| CAC increasing while LTV flat \| Unit economics degrading \| op conversion or reduce sales cycle \|
M|Unit|tx|\| Contribution margin <40% \| Unprofitable after variable costs \| Cut variable costs or increase prices \|
M|Capi|tx|\| **Red Flag** \| **What It Means** \| **Action** \|
M|Capi|tx|\|--------------\|-------------------\|------------\|
M|Capi|tx|\| Runway <6 months \| Survival crisis \| Raise capital immediately or cut burn \|
M|Capi|tx|\| Net burn accelerating w/o rv growth \| Burning faster w/o results \| Cut costs or increase rv urgency \|
M|Capi|tx|\| OpEx growing faster than rv \| Negative operating leverage \| Freeze hiring; op spend \|
M|Capi|tx|\| Rule of 40 <25 \| Burning cash w/o growth \| Improve growth or cut to profitability \|
M|Capi|tx|\| Magic Number <0.5 \| S&M engine broken \| Fix GTM efficiency before scaling spend \|
M|Capi|tx|---
M|When|**Pr|**
M|When|it|rv impact → rv, ARPU, Expansion rv
M|When|it|Margin impact → Gross Margin, Contribution Margin
M|When|it|ROI → LTV impact, dv cost
M|When|**Ev|**
M|When|it|Acquisition cost → CAC, CAC by Channel
M|When|it|cs value → LTV, NRR by Channel
M|When|it|Payback → Payback Period, CAC Payback by Channel
M|When|it|Scalability → Magic Number
M|When|**Pr|**
M|When|it|Monetization → ARPU, ARPA, ACV
M|When|it|Impact → Churn Rate, NRR, Expansion rv
M|When|it|Efficiency → CAC Payback (will pricing change affect it?)
M|When|**Bu|**
M|When|it|Growth → rv Growth, MRR/ARR Growth
M|When|it|Retention → Churn Rate, NRR, Quick Ratio
M|When|- Ec|CAC, Payback Period, Gross Margin
M|When|it|Efficiency → Rule of 40, Magic Number, Operating Leverage
M|When|it|Survival → Burn Rate, Runway
M|When|**Bo|**
M|When|- Ke|ARR, rv Growth %, NRR, LTV:CAC, Rule of 40, Magic Number, Burn Rate, Runway
M|When|- St|Early stage emphasize growth + unit economics; Growth stage emphasize Rule of 40 + Magic Number; Scale stage emphasize profitability + efficiency
M|When|tx|---
M|Exam|tx|You are deciding whether to bd a premium export feature.
M|Exam|tx|1. Use Framework 1 (shd We bd This Feature?)
M|Exam|2. P|ARPU, Gross Margin, LTV, Contribution Margin
M|Exam|tx|3. md optimistic, base, and downside adoption
M|Exam|tx|4. Reject if contribution margin turns negative in downside case
M|Exam|Quic|
M|Exam|- Ba|3.8x
M|Exam|- Co|+4 points
M|Exam|- De|bd now, w/ a 90-day post-launch check on churn and expansion
M|Exam|tx|Paid sl is generating many signups but weak retention.
M|Exam|tx|1. Use Framework 2 (shd We Scale This Acquisition Channel?)
M|Exam|2. C|CAC, Payback Period, and NRR by channel
M|Exam|tx|3. Compare against best-performing channel, not company average
M|Exam|Quic|
M|Exam|- LT|CAC: 1.6:1
M|Exam|- Pa|26 months
M|Exam|- NR|88%
M|Exam|- De|Do not scale; cap spend and run targeted op tests
M|Exam|tx|---
M|Comm|it|Using blended company averages instead of cohort or channel-level metrics
M|Comm|it|Scaling acquisition when Quick Ratio is weak and retention is deteriorating
M|Comm|- Tr|CAC as sufficient w/o checking payback and runway impact
M|Comm|it|Raising prices based on ARPU lift alone w/o modeling churn and contraction
M|Comm|it|Comparing benchmarks across mismatched company stages or business md
M|Comm|it|Tracking many metrics w/o a clear decision question
